@baude I can confirm my testing and ouput are from the official Podman CLI installer.

2020 Macbook Pro here (although I just noticed I'm on Sequia 15.2).

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c4836b9c-1624-4044-8648-77895c9c22a0)

Using the above script, I rolled the FC41 Cloud image forward to what appears to be the last fc41 kernel build in the 6.11 series, 6.11.11-300 successfully. The first non-deleted kernel build in the 6.12 series appears to be .3-200 [according to this list](https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/packageinfo?buildStart=100&packageID=8&buildOrder=-completion_time&tagOrder=name&tagStart=0#buildlist), which immediately breaks it.

So yes, it does appear to be a 6.12 thing even though [@dustymabe's rebuild of the current OS image with a 6.11 kernel reversion](https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/25121#issuecomment-2686330662) did not boot as hoped.

@cfergeau, my concerns over NAT were misplaced. At the time I posted that, I hadn't realized yet that the NAT interface would be created on localhost, allowing me to access it from the local machine, if not from anywhere else.
